{
  "text": "A very high cell concentration was reached in beads (10 11 CFU g -1 beads) leading to a high total population, including immobilized and free cells, of [CITATION_1] 13 CFU per litre of reactor similar to that reported by Doleyres et al. [CITATION_2] with immobilized B. longum cells in gellan gum beads during continuous culture operated at a dilution rate of 0.5 h -1 . As a comparison, batch cultures with free cells of B. longum NCC2705 generally reach 10 9 CFU ml -1 , corresponding to 10 12 CFU per litre of reactor at the end of the culture (data not shown). This high cell density could favor the occurrence of mutations since the rate of appearance of mutational events is proportional to the amount of biomass in the culture [CITATION_3] .",
